snippet.textDisplay:
Osu should have gone for it on 4th down in the red zone. When will coaches stop settling for field goals early in games? 3 points might mean a lot in the fourth but you are better off gambling for the td earlier in the game.

And if you fail on 4th down in the red zone you usually make the opposing offence drive the length of the field and it’s hard to operate close to your own end zone.

Coaches need to start going for it on fourth down at around the opposing 40 yard line and near the end zone. Punt when you are between your end And about the opposing 40 and kick FGs when you reach 4th down in between the opposing 40 and the opposing 10.

In late game situations it might make more sense to kick the fg depending on the situation
